{
  "text": "Smc2p is a DNA-binding subunit of the Smc2p/Smc4p condensin complex 55, 56, 57 required for sister chromatid (SC) alignment, separation, and inhibiting SC recombination during mitosis 55, [CITATION_1] . We identified four strong dosage suppressors of smc2: UME1, MEK1, HTA2, and SNU66 (Fig. 5a ). Strikingly, the first two are known to play mutually opposing functional roles [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] -UME1 is a mitotically expressed gene required for the repression of a subset of meiotic genes, including those important for meiotic homologous recombination, and MEK1 is a meiosis specific protein kinase that promotes meiotic homologous recombination by suppressing sister chromatid (SC) recombination.",
